	Annotations: bim:Definition "It declares the UUID (Universally Unique Identifier). Formed by 128 bits (16 bytes). It is a string of 32 hexadecimal characters xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx. Implemented and published by the IETF (Internet Engineering Task Force). It's Multiplatform."@en
	Characteristics: Functional
	Characteristics: InverseFunctional
	EquivalentTo: bim:é.guid

